WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.100 --> 00:00:06.270
The Hooded Man is one of the.. strangest mysteries
in Game of Thrones.

00:00:06.270 --> 00:00:09.300
In the latest book, the Boltons have Winterfell.

00:00:09.300 --> 00:00:12.810
But Stannis Baratheon's army is coming to
attack them.

00:00:12.810 --> 00:00:18.320
So the Boltons rally their own army, with
the Freys and northern allies, crowding thousands

00:00:18.320 --> 00:00:20.510
of soldiers into Winterfell.

00:00:20.510 --> 00:00:23.940
And as a snowstorm falls, tensions rise.

00:00:23.940 --> 00:00:29.100
Cause these northern houses say they support
the Boltons, but most of them actually hate

00:00:29.100 --> 00:00:33.870
the Boltons – cause the Boltons and Freys
betrayed the Starks and killed hundreds of

00:00:33.870 --> 00:00:39.719
northmen at the Red Wedding – “The north
remembers” these Bolton crimes , so some

00:00:39.719 --> 00:00:42.719
northern lords plan to betray the Boltons.

00:00:42.719 --> 00:00:48.639
We know Wyman Manderly is against the Boltons
, and the Umbers and Dustins might be too.

00:00:48.639 --> 00:00:53.859
Ramsay marries a girl who the Boltons say
is Arya Stark , though she’s actually a

00:00:53.859 --> 00:00:55.289
girl called Jeyne.

00:00:55.289 --> 00:01:00.819
Mance Rayder and six wildling women infiltrate
Winterfell to rescue this girl.

00:01:00.819 --> 00:01:07.659
And Theon Greyjoy wanders the castle like
a ghost, broken by Ramsay’s torture.

00:01:07.659 --> 00:01:12.840
And all the while, Stannis and his army are
camped in the snow nearby.

00:01:12.840 --> 00:01:15.770
So there’s a lot going on in Winterfell.

00:01:15.770 --> 00:01:22.439
The Bolton-Frey-northern alliance is dangerously
unstable , the castle is full of plots, secrets,

00:01:22.439 --> 00:01:28.880
and lies – and a mysterious murderer walks
the castle at night.

00:01:28.880 --> 00:01:34.750
One morning, they find a dead man in Winterfell
– a Ryswell soldier with a broken neck,

00:01:34.750 --> 00:01:36.439
half-buried in the snow.

00:01:36.439 --> 00:01:42.400
Then, a dead Frey squire is found naked in
the castle graveyard , and a dead Flint soldier

00:01:42.400 --> 00:01:44.140
in the stables.

00:01:44.140 --> 00:01:48.590
Then one of Ramsay’s friends is killed,
a man called Yellow Dick.

00:01:48.590 --> 00:01:54.180
His dick was cut off and “stuffed … into
his mouth” so hard that his teeth broke.

00:01:54.180 --> 00:02:00.710
These murders get everyone suspicious, rumours
fly, and tensions rise between the northmen

00:02:00.710 --> 00:02:02.370
and the Freys.

00:02:02.370 --> 00:02:05.119
It really hits the fan after the fifth murder.

00:02:05.119 --> 00:02:10.030
Cause this victim isn’t just some random
soldier, it’s “Little” Walder Frey,

00:02:10.030 --> 00:02:13.810
the nine-year-old grandson of Lord Walder
Frey.

00:02:13.810 --> 00:02:18.501
The Freys accuse Wyman of the murder, and
the Freys and Manderlys start fighting, so

00:02:18.501 --> 00:02:23.500
to stop his army destroying itself, Roose
Bolton orders the Freys and Manderlys to go

00:02:23.500 --> 00:02:29.350
and attack Stannis , which is actually exactly
what Stannis wants – Stannis seems to be

00:02:29.350 --> 00:02:33.860
planning a trap for the Freys , which is explained
in our Pink Letter video.

00:02:33.860 --> 00:02:39.750
So these Winterfell murders may be a deliberate
plan to create conflict in Winterfell , to

00:02:39.750 --> 00:02:42.890
lure the Boltons into Stannis’ trap.

00:02:42.890 --> 00:02:48.650
Cause these five victims aren't random – they
seem very deliberately targeted.

00:02:48.650 --> 00:02:53.040
Cause most of the houses in Winterfell hate
the Boltons.

00:02:53.040 --> 00:02:58.880
The only ones that seem genuinely loyal to
the Boltons are the Freys, and the Ryswells.

00:02:58.880 --> 00:03:04.290
And those are the houses that get murdered
– Roger Ryswell's groom, Aenys Frey’s

00:03:04.290 --> 00:03:08.300
squire, Little Walder, and Ramsay’s friend.

00:03:08.300 --> 00:03:12.920
All these victims are close to a lord who’s
loyal to the Boltons.

00:03:12.920 --> 00:03:18.080
Except for this Flint soldier – the Flints
are a minor house, and we don’t know much

00:03:18.080 --> 00:03:19.110
about them.

00:03:19.110 --> 00:03:24.480
So maybe this Flint guy really was just “Kicked
by a horse” in the stables, and wasn’t

00:03:24.480 --> 00:03:25.480
murdered.

00:03:25.480 --> 00:03:29.760
But overall, these murders seem deliberately
targeted to piss off the Boltons and Freys,

00:03:29.760 --> 00:03:33.780
to create conflict, to help Stannis beat the
Boltons.

00:03:33.780 --> 00:03:39.110
The lords think the murderer must be working
for Stannis , or working for Wyman Manderly.

00:03:39.110 --> 00:03:43.660
Some think Theon is be the killer , but they
decide it can’t be Theon, cause he’s too

00:03:43.660 --> 00:03:48.670
weak – in the books, Ramsay’s torture
destroys Theon’s body.

00:03:48.670 --> 00:03:54.420
He’s starved and frail , with missing fingers
and toes , and he’s psychologically broken

00:03:54.420 --> 00:03:58.020
– he doesn’t have the strength to murder
five men.

00:03:58.020 --> 00:04:00.870
So who is the killer?

00:04:00.870 --> 00:04:05.780
Amidst the murders, Theon wanders Winterfell
aimless and alone.

00:04:05.780 --> 00:04:10.790
And one night, he sees a mysterious man in
a hooded cloak.

00:04:10.790 --> 00:04:15.710
The man recognises Theon, and calls him a
“Turncloak” and a “Kinslayer” – many

00:04:15.710 --> 00:04:21.459
northmen hate “Theon Turncloak” because
Theon betrayed the Starks and took Winterfell.

00:04:21.459 --> 00:04:26.680
Calling Theon a “Kinslayer” is unusual,
but it’s because everyone thinks that Theon

00:04:26.680 --> 00:04:32.290
killed Bran and Rickon Stark, who were Theon’s
“foster brothers” – so even though Theon

00:04:32.290 --> 00:04:38.240
and the Starks weren’t kin as in blood relatives,
it’s still kind of kinslaying.

00:04:38.240 --> 00:04:42.880
The Hooded Man puts a hand on his dagger , as
though he might attack Theon, but when Theon

00:04:42.880 --> 00:04:49.840
shows him his disfigured tortured hands , the
man laughs and leaves Theon to his torment.

00:04:49.840 --> 00:04:55.310
So Theon thinks this Hooded Man might be the
murderer in Winterfell – why else would

00:04:55.310 --> 00:04:59.050
he be striding around at night, with his cloak
and dagger?

00:04:59.050 --> 00:05:03.360
And the hooded man might not be working alone.

00:05:03.360 --> 00:05:08.770
There are only three characters in the series
who call Theon a kinslayer.

00:05:08.770 --> 00:05:13.570
First is the Hooded Man, then there’s Rowan
, one of the wildlings who helps Theon and

00:05:13.570 --> 00:05:15.740
Jeyne escape Winterfell.

00:05:15.740 --> 00:05:20.440
Then there’s Crowfood Umber – a northman
working for Stannis, who rescues Theon and

00:05:20.440 --> 00:05:22.260
Jeyne outside Winterfell.

00:05:22.260 --> 00:05:27.620
It’s very convenient that Crowfood just
happened to be outside Winterfell to grab

00:05:27.620 --> 00:05:31.010
Theon when Rowan helped him escape.

00:05:31.010 --> 00:05:35.610
So there’s a theory that Rowan and Crowfood
are connected.

00:05:35.610 --> 00:05:41.660
Rowan really hates Theon for supposedly killing
Bran and Rickon – she spits in Theon’s

00:05:41.660 --> 00:05:46.330
face and says he wasn’t punished enough
for killing the Starks.

00:05:46.330 --> 00:05:49.720
Which is weird, cause Rowan’s a wildling.

00:05:49.720 --> 00:05:53.570
The Starks and the wildlings have been enemies
for centuries.

00:05:53.570 --> 00:05:58.400
Yet Rowan makes a respectful comment about
“Lord Eddard’s words”.

00:05:58.400 --> 00:06:02.020
Why does this wildling respect Ned Stark?

00:06:02.020 --> 00:06:07.430
It’s mentioned that Crowfood Umber once
had a daughter who “was carried off by wildlings

00:06:07.430 --> 00:06:08.900
thirty years ago”.

00:06:08.900 --> 00:06:11.760
So maybe Rowan is that daughter.

00:06:11.760 --> 00:06:16.580
The Umbers are loyal to the Starks, so if
Rowan was raised as an Umber, that would explain

00:06:16.580 --> 00:06:22.139
why she respects Ned Stark, and why she hates
Theon for killing Ned Starks’s sons, and

00:06:22.139 --> 00:06:27.870
why she’s risking her life to save the girl
who she thinks is Ned Stark’s daughter.

00:06:27.870 --> 00:06:33.139
If Rowan is Crowfood’s daughter, they might’ve
been working together on this rescue – and

00:06:33.139 --> 00:06:36.910
that’s why Crowfood was outside the walls
at the right time.

00:06:36.910 --> 00:06:39.630
And the hooded man might also be involved.

00:06:39.630 --> 00:06:45.400
Cause the hooded man appears on the same night
that Crowfood arrives outside Winterfell – maybe

00:06:45.400 --> 00:06:47.090
they came together.

00:06:47.090 --> 00:06:53.580
And Crowfood calls Theon a turncloak and kinslayer
just like the hooded man calls him turncloak

00:06:53.580 --> 00:06:55.360
and kinslayer.

00:06:55.360 --> 00:07:01.730
Maybe the hooded man, Rowan and Crowfood are
all working together, to rescue Arya, and

00:07:01.730 --> 00:07:06.150
to murder soldiers to help Stannis beat the
Boltons.

00:07:06.150 --> 00:07:10.320
Remember that Rowan and the wildlings were
sent to Winterfell by Melisandre, who works

00:07:10.320 --> 00:07:13.960
for Stannis, just like Crowfood works for
Stannis.

00:07:13.960 --> 00:07:21.360
So how does the hooded man fit in this conspiracy
– and who is the Hooded Man?

00:07:21.360 --> 00:07:26.210
One possibility is Robett Glover, the brother
of Lord Galbart Glover.

00:07:26.210 --> 00:07:29.270
The Glover brothers fought for Robb Stark
in his war.

00:07:29.270 --> 00:07:35.150
But then Robett was screwed over by Roose
Bolton, who sent Robett into a trap at Duskendale.

00:07:35.150 --> 00:07:40.870
Meanwhile, Robett’s wife and children got
captured by Asha Greyjoy, who still has his

00:07:40.870 --> 00:07:44.000
kids as hostages on the Iron Islands.

00:07:44.000 --> 00:07:49.630
In Book 5, Robett works with Wyman Manderly
in his secret plan to betray the Boltons and

00:07:49.630 --> 00:07:51.229
help Stannis.

00:07:51.229 --> 00:07:57.580
So Robett’s already in an anti-Bolton conspiracy
– maybe he came with Wyman to Winterfell,

00:07:57.580 --> 00:08:02.070
and became the hooded man – committing those
murders, and maybe working with Crowfood and

00:08:02.070 --> 00:08:03.140
Rowan.

00:08:03.140 --> 00:08:07.919
When Robett plots with Wyman, Robett wears
a cloak , and uses a dagger – like the Hooded

00:08:07.919 --> 00:08:10.340
Man has a cloak and dagger.

00:08:10.340 --> 00:08:15.120
And it makes sense that the hooded man really
hates Theon Turncloak – cause the Greyjoy

00:08:15.120 --> 00:08:19.490
invasion of the north cost Robett his family
and home.

00:08:19.490 --> 00:08:26.460
So Robett Glover fits – he could be hooded
man – but there is a problem with this theory.

00:08:26.460 --> 00:08:30.950
Cause Robett Glover knows that Bran and Rickon
are alive.

00:08:30.950 --> 00:08:35.979
So if Robett is the hooded man, and he knows
Theon didn’t kill the Starks, why would

00:08:35.979 --> 00:08:37.849
he call Theon “Kinslayer”?

00:08:37.849 --> 00:08:43.209
You could argue that Theon is a kinslayer
cause he got some ironborn killed at Moat

00:08:43.209 --> 00:08:44.209
Cailin.

00:08:44.209 --> 00:08:48.920
And there is a crazy theory that Theon killed
his own sons – which.. we’ll get to.

00:08:48.920 --> 00:08:52.970
But it doesn’t make much sense for Robett
to call Theon “Kinslayer”.

00:08:52.970 --> 00:08:56.589
So who else could be the Hooded Man?

00:08:56.589 --> 00:08:59.019
Harwin was one of Ned Stark’s guards.

00:08:59.019 --> 00:09:04.180
He used to help Arya Jon and Robb learn to
ride horses – he’s a trusted and loyal

00:09:04.180 --> 00:09:06.360
servant of House Stark.

00:09:06.360 --> 00:09:11.529
In Book 1, Harwin was sent on a mission with
Beric and Thoros – but they were attacked,

00:09:11.529 --> 00:09:14.829
and the group became the brotherhood without
banners.

00:09:14.829 --> 00:09:19.560
When Arya meets the brotherhood, she reunites
with Harwin – and it’s an emotional moment,

00:09:19.560 --> 00:09:23.560
with Arya and Harwin reconnecting with their
past lives at Winterfell.

00:09:23.560 --> 00:09:30.129
Harwin’s fond of Arya, and protective of
her, but they split when Arya leaves the brotherhood.

00:09:30.129 --> 00:09:35.220
In Book 4, Harwin’s in the brotherhood group
led by Lady Stoneheart – the resurrected

00:09:35.220 --> 00:09:37.740
corpse of Catelyn Stark.

00:09:37.740 --> 00:09:42.970
Stoneheart seems to be searching for her daughter
Arya, questioning captives about her.

00:09:42.970 --> 00:09:48.259
And by now, Stoneheart must have heard the
news that Arya has married Ramsay Bolton.

00:09:48.259 --> 00:09:51.850
So maybe Stoneheart sent someone to rescue
Arya.

00:09:51.850 --> 00:09:56.709
And Harwin is the perfect man for the job
– he knows Arya, he knows Winterfell, he’s

00:09:56.709 --> 00:09:58.200
loyal to the Starks.

00:09:58.200 --> 00:10:03.189
So maybe Harwin went to Winterfell – and
when he realised Ramsay’s bride isn’t

00:10:03.189 --> 00:10:08.529
really Arya, he coulda become the hooded man
– murdering Boltons, getting involved with

00:10:08.529 --> 00:10:11.120
Rowan and Wyman’s conspiracies.

00:10:11.120 --> 00:10:15.550
Since Harwin knew Theon and the Starks as
they grew up together, so it makes sense that

00:10:15.550 --> 00:10:22.490
Harwin would see Bran and Rickon as Theon’s
brothers, and would hate Theon as a kinslayer.

00:10:22.490 --> 00:10:27.160
An argument against Harwin is that he and
Theon knew each other for years – so why

00:10:27.160 --> 00:10:29.290
doesn’t Theon recognise Harwin?

00:10:29.290 --> 00:10:35.339
It’s not like the Hooded Man’s hood covers
his face, because Theon and the man come “face-to-face”

00:10:35.339 --> 00:10:37.529
and “their eyes [meet]”.

00:10:37.529 --> 00:10:42.999
Then again, Theon fails to recognise his own
sister earlier – mistaken identities are

00:10:42.999 --> 00:10:44.890
a theme in his story.

00:10:44.890 --> 00:10:49.230
And Arya has trouble recognising Harwin – cause
he’s thinner and got a new beard.

00:10:49.230 --> 00:10:52.730
So maybe Theon just didn’t recognise Harwin.

00:10:52.730 --> 00:10:58.309
Harwin might be the hooded man – originally
on a mission to save Arya, and now involved

00:10:58.309 --> 00:11:01.699
in murder and conspiracy in Winterfell.

00:11:01.699 --> 00:11:06.560
And unlike Robett Glover, Harwin has an emotional
connection to the Stark characters, so it

00:11:06.560 --> 00:11:11.009
could be a more meaningful reveal if he’s
the hooded man.

00:11:11.009 --> 00:11:15.470
Another possibility is Hallis Mollen, another
Winterfell guard.

00:11:15.470 --> 00:11:21.379
He guards Catelyn Stark during Robb’s war
in the south , until Catelyn gets Ned Stark’s

00:11:21.379 --> 00:11:22.379
bones.

00:11:22.379 --> 00:11:27.040
She wants her husband’s bones to rest in
the crypt at Winterfell, so she sends Hal

00:11:27.040 --> 00:11:29.000
to take the bones north.

00:11:29.000 --> 00:11:34.699
But as far as we know, Hal never arrives at
Winterfell – Catelyn thinks Hal might’ve

00:11:34.699 --> 00:11:37.749
been blocked off from the north at Moat Cailin.

00:11:37.749 --> 00:11:42.329
In Winterfell, Barbrey Dustin tells Theon
that she’s watching for Ned’s bones, cause

00:11:42.329 --> 00:11:49.160
she wants to feed them to her dogs – but
Barbrey hasn’t found the bones either.

00:11:49.160 --> 00:11:51.149
So where is Hal?

00:11:51.149 --> 00:11:56.500
If he was blocked at Moat Cailin, he could’ve
ended up in nearby Greywater Watch, the home

00:11:56.500 --> 00:12:01.959
of Howland Reed, who happens to be the one
man alive who would know that Jon Snow is

00:12:01.959 --> 00:12:04.309
the son of Prince Rhaegar.

00:12:04.309 --> 00:12:09.110
Also last we saw Robett’s brother Galbart
Glover, he was sent to Howland Reed – and

00:12:09.110 --> 00:12:13.629
Galbart knows about Robb Stark’s will that
makes Jon King in the North.

00:12:13.629 --> 00:12:18.980
The point is that Hal could get involved in
a bunch of potential conspiracies.

00:12:18.980 --> 00:12:24.660
And if Hal did eventually make it to Winterfell,
he could play the role of the Hooded Man – killing

00:12:24.660 --> 00:12:28.630
Bolton soldiers, returning Ned’s bones.

00:12:28.630 --> 00:12:33.239
Like Harwin, Hal knew Theon and the Starks
as they grew up, so it makes sense that Hal

00:12:33.239 --> 00:12:35.450
would hate Theon as a “Kinslayer”.

00:12:35.450 --> 00:12:41.059
But Hal’s personality might be a problem
– he has “a loose tongue” , and tends

00:12:41.059 --> 00:12:43.440
to “loudly” “[state] the obvious”.

00:12:43.440 --> 00:12:48.410
He doesn’t sound like the ideal person for
a secret hooded mission?

00:12:48.410 --> 00:12:52.329
But it’s possible that Hal is the hooded
man.

00:12:52.329 --> 00:12:58.639
So Hal or Harwin or maybe Robett Glover could
all could be the Hooded Man –. Some fans

00:12:58.639 --> 00:13:02.959
think that Brynden Blackfish, or Benjen Stark
could be the Hooded Man.

00:13:02.959 --> 00:13:08.350
It could kind of be anyone who loved the Starks,
and maybe that’s the point.

00:13:08.350 --> 00:13:13.040
One of the themes in the story is that even
though the Starks are defeated, their legacy

00:13:13.040 --> 00:13:14.209
lives on.

00:13:14.209 --> 00:13:20.000
“The north remembers” Ned Stark's leadership,
and that's why so many northmen still fight

00:13:20.000 --> 00:13:24.470
and die in his name , and are trying to save
his daughter.

00:13:24.470 --> 00:13:29.779
Maybe the Hooded Man is the embodiment of
the north’s loyalty, living proof that the

00:13:29.779 --> 00:13:31.639
north remembers.

00:13:31.639 --> 00:13:35.620
He could be just an unnamed unknown northman.

00:13:35.620 --> 00:13:37.569
Maybe it doesn’t matter who’s under the
hood.

00:13:37.569 --> 00:13:41.480
[like V for Vendetta]
But here’s the thing – whoever the Hooded

00:13:41.480 --> 00:13:47.829
Man is, he’s probably not the Winterfell
murderer – the wildlings are.

00:13:47.829 --> 00:13:53.170
Jon Snow and Melisandre sent Mance and these
women to Winterfell, to rescue Jeyne, who

00:13:53.170 --> 00:13:54.660
they think is Arya.

00:13:54.660 --> 00:14:00.339
But even if Rowan is an Umber, there’s no
way all these wildlings would risk their lives

00:14:00.339 --> 00:14:03.089
just to save Arya Stark.

00:14:03.089 --> 00:14:09.370
Jon thinks they must have some other hidden
plan in Winterfell – which is probably to

00:14:09.370 --> 00:14:13.319
help Stannis beat the Boltons by murdering
these soldiers.

00:14:13.319 --> 00:14:18.379
We know these wildling women can fight – they
kill several guards while Theon and Jeyne

00:14:18.379 --> 00:14:20.230
escape.

00:14:20.230 --> 00:14:25.579
Theon accuses the women of the murders , and
Rowan says they didn’t kill Little Walder

00:14:25.579 --> 00:14:30.709
, but she basically admits that they did kill
Yellow Dick and the others.

00:14:30.709 --> 00:14:35.860
In the escape, the women use their sexuality
to get guards in a vulnerable positions so

00:14:35.860 --> 00:14:37.379
they can kill them.

00:14:37.379 --> 00:14:41.800
And they probably used the same strategy on
these murder victims – like, Yellow Dick

00:14:41.800 --> 00:14:46.490
has his cock is his mouth, and this Frey squire
is found “naked” – the women must have

00:14:46.490 --> 00:14:49.899
lured these men with sex before killing them.

00:14:49.899 --> 00:14:51.910
That explains most of these murders.

00:14:51.910 --> 00:14:56.790
But what about Little Walder – if the wildlings
didn’t kill him, who did?

00:14:56.790 --> 00:15:02.490
There's a theory that Little Walder was killed
by his cousin Big Walder.

00:15:02.490 --> 00:15:07.499
Big Walder is just nine years old , but he’s
ambitious and brutal.

00:15:07.499 --> 00:15:12.019
He’s always talking about the line of succession
in House Frey, and how he’s determined to

00:15:12.019 --> 00:15:14.170
become Lord of the Crossing.

00:15:14.170 --> 00:15:19.299
And it sounds like he’s willing to kill
for it – he talks casually about murdering

00:15:19.299 --> 00:15:20.519
other Freys.

00:15:20.519 --> 00:15:25.529
And when Little Walder’s body is found,
Big Walder’s gloves are “caked with his

00:15:25.529 --> 00:15:29.829
cousin’s blood” – bloody hands are a
classic symbol of guilt.

00:15:29.829 --> 00:15:35.300
So it seems likely that Big Walder killed
Little Walder to move up the line of succession.

00:15:35.300 --> 00:15:40.779
The wildlings killed Yellow Dick and the Ryswell
and Frey as part of their conspiracy, and

00:15:40.779 --> 00:15:44.670
this poor Flint guy was probably just kicked
by a horse.

00:15:44.670 --> 00:15:46.980
Murder mystery solved.

00:15:46.980 --> 00:15:51.949
But if these are the murderers, what’s the
point of the Hooded Man?

00:15:51.949 --> 00:15:58.800
Like he could just be helping Rowan and Crowfood
or Wyman or something, but surely this mysterious

00:15:58.800 --> 00:16:01.850
figure has some deeper meaning.

00:16:01.850 --> 00:16:08.709
Theon’s story in this book is about escaping
his identity as Reek, and becoming Theon Greyjoy

00:16:08.709 --> 00:16:09.929
again.

00:16:09.929 --> 00:16:15.149
Reek is broken – weak and afraid and obedient
to Ramsay.

00:16:15.149 --> 00:16:20.559
Theon is the man he used to be – proud and
strong, a Greyjoy.

00:16:20.559 --> 00:16:25.790
Ramsay’s torture and control has forced
him to supress his identity as Theon.

00:16:25.790 --> 00:16:29.010
Reek thinks of Theon as a different person
to himself.

00:16:29.010 --> 00:16:35.819
“Theon Greyjoy died”, and Reek is a new
man , born in Ramsay’s dungeon.

00:16:35.819 --> 00:16:43.109
While Theon struggles with this identity crisis
, he’s haunted by “ghosts” – Winterfell

00:16:43.109 --> 00:16:46.209
is “full of ghosts for Theon Greyjoy”.

00:16:46.209 --> 00:16:51.769
Cause Winterfell is where Theon grew up with
the Starks – and it’s where he betrayed

00:16:51.769 --> 00:16:54.410
the Starks when he took their castle.

00:16:54.410 --> 00:17:01.589
Theon killed northmen and ironborn here, people
who trusted him – and their “ghosts”

00:17:01.589 --> 00:17:02.980
are “angry”.

00:17:02.980 --> 00:17:09.459
Theon hears ghostly voices in the godswood
, and he sees Bran’s face in a weirwood

00:17:09.459 --> 00:17:10.459
tree.

00:17:10.459 --> 00:17:16.149
So with all his guilt and trauma, Theon is
seeing stuff, he’s hearing voices, he’s

00:17:16.149 --> 00:17:22.770
haunted by ghosts, he doesn’t know who he
is, in this crisis between Theon and Reek.

00:17:22.770 --> 00:17:28.439
And it’s during this crisis that Theon sees
the hooded man – he comes “face-to-face”

00:17:28.439 --> 00:17:34.580
with this mysterious figure “alone” in
the snow , and strangely, Theon is “not

00:17:34.580 --> 00:17:35.580
afraid”.

00:17:35.580 --> 00:17:43.000
There’s a theory that the hooded man is
a ghost – a vision or hallucination in Theon’s

00:17:43.000 --> 00:17:47.971
tortured mind, and a representation of his
identity crisis – like, maybe the hooded

00:17:47.971 --> 00:17:52.240
man is the ghost of who Theon used to be.

00:17:52.240 --> 00:17:57.720
The hooded man acts a lot like Theon once
did – he’s confident, and purposeful,

00:17:57.720 --> 00:17:59.049
and kind of a dick.

00:17:59.049 --> 00:18:03.240
Cause the man laughs at Theon’s disfigured
hand.

00:18:03.240 --> 00:18:05.960
Which is like how Theon used to laugh at people.

00:18:05.960 --> 00:18:11.019
Like, in the TV show, Theon kind of always
was a sensitive sad boy.

00:18:11.019 --> 00:18:17.570
But in the books, Theon started as this confident
smug, sometimes cruel young man.

00:18:17.570 --> 00:18:24.031
He was known his “sly smile” and his mocking
contemptuous laugh – just like the hooded

00:18:24.031 --> 00:18:27.260
man laughs at Theon’s misfortune.

00:18:27.260 --> 00:18:32.809
Also in Book 2, at the height of Theon’s
confidence and pride, he wore a hooded cloak

00:18:32.809 --> 00:18:34.990
, like the hooded man.

00:18:34.990 --> 00:18:41.750
Maybe by facing the hooded man, Reek faces
the ghost of Theon Greyjoy, as part of his

00:18:41.750 --> 00:18:45.100
journey from Reek back to Theon.

00:18:45.100 --> 00:18:52.010
The ghost also represents his guilt and self-hatred
– cause the man is hostile, accusing Theon

00:18:52.010 --> 00:18:53.399
of his crimes.

00:18:53.399 --> 00:18:58.470
It’s like the ghosts in Shakespeare – in
Hamlet and Macbeth, characters are haunted

00:18:58.470 --> 00:19:04.320
by ghosts which represent the characters’
inner conflicts, guilts and doubts.

00:19:04.320 --> 00:19:06.880
The hooded man could also represent death.

00:19:06.880 --> 00:19:13.210
In the Faith of the Seven, the god of death
appears as a hooded man called the Stranger.

00:19:13.210 --> 00:19:19.480
This hooded man is a Stranger, who threatens
Theon – but Theon defies him, saying “The

00:19:19.480 --> 00:19:21.429
gods are not done with me”.

00:19:21.429 --> 00:19:28.740
Theon faces death and tells him ‘not today’
– instead choosing life as Theon, and escaping

00:19:28.740 --> 00:19:29.990
Winterfell.

00:19:29.990 --> 00:19:35.230
So the hooded man is an important moment in
Theon’s character arc from Reek to Theon.

00:19:35.230 --> 00:19:40.630
Given the psychological turmoil Theon’s
in, and all the talk of ghosts, it’s possible

00:19:40.630 --> 00:19:46.059
that this hooded man is some kinda vision
or hallucination.

00:19:46.059 --> 00:19:49.049
But there are problems with this theory.

00:19:49.049 --> 00:19:51.730
The Hooded Man calls Theon a kinslayer.

00:19:51.730 --> 00:19:57.789
But Theon thinks he’s not a kinslayer, because
he didn’t actually kill Bran and Rickon.

00:19:57.789 --> 00:20:03.460
If the Hooded Man is just in Theon’s mind,
why would he accuse himself of a crime he

00:20:03.460 --> 00:20:09.360
didn’t commit ? There is a theory that Theon
is a kinslayer after all.

00:20:09.360 --> 00:20:13.250
Cause in Book 2, Theon fails to find Bran
and Rickon.

00:20:13.250 --> 00:20:18.950
So instead, Theon kills two other boys of
the same age, and burns them, and says their

00:20:18.950 --> 00:20:21.529
bodies are Bran and Rickon’s.

00:20:21.529 --> 00:20:25.610
The mother of these boys is a woman called
the miller’s wife.

00:20:25.610 --> 00:20:29.059
And Theon mentions that he had sex with her
a couple times.

00:20:29.059 --> 00:20:36.220
So maybe one or both of the children Theon
killed are actually Theon’s sons.

00:20:36.220 --> 00:20:41.559
In Book 2, Ygritte tells the story of a man
who unknowingly killed his own father – she

00:20:41.559 --> 00:20:46.840
says “the gods hate kinslayers, even when
they kill unknowing”.

00:20:46.840 --> 00:20:52.279
If Theon unknowingly murdered his own children,
it’s similar to how he unknowingly tried

00:20:52.279 --> 00:20:58.210
to have sex with his own sister – there’s
an Oedipal Freudian thing going on here.

00:20:58.210 --> 00:21:02.389
Maybe, deep down, Theon knows that the kids
were his.

00:21:02.389 --> 00:21:07.470
And he supresses this deep dark secret to
his subconscious, not wanting to believe he’s

00:21:07.470 --> 00:21:08.870
a kinslayer.

00:21:08.870 --> 00:21:14.240
At one point he tries not to remember something
about these boys – “There were things

00:21:14.240 --> 00:21:17.120
too hurtful to remember”.

00:21:17.120 --> 00:21:23.389
Maybe the hooded man calling Theon “Kinslayer”
is the externalisation of that supressed memory,

00:21:23.389 --> 00:21:25.509
a subconscious spectre of guilt.

00:21:25.509 --> 00:21:32.169
It’s a cool theory, but there’s not much
evidence that the sons are Theon’s.

00:21:32.169 --> 00:21:35.909
And you’d think that if it was true, it
would’ve been revealed by the end of the

00:21:35.909 --> 00:21:37.929
book, when Reek became Theon.

00:21:37.929 --> 00:21:44.260
So maybe the real meaning of the of the kinslayer
stuff is to explore the question of who Theon’s

00:21:44.260 --> 00:21:48.399
kin is – were the Starks his family , or
the ironborn?

00:21:48.399 --> 00:21:50.030
Was Winterfell his home?

00:21:50.030 --> 00:21:54.720
Did he betray the only people who ever loved
him?

00:21:54.720 --> 00:21:59.870
These are the questions at the heart of Theon’s
arc, and that’s probably why this kinslayer

00:21:59.870 --> 00:22:01.980
idea keeps coming up.

00:22:01.980 --> 00:22:07.120
But if Theon didn’t slay his kin, it doesn’t
make sense for Theon’s ghost to call him

00:22:07.120 --> 00:22:08.120
“Kinslayer”.

00:22:08.120 --> 00:22:10.779
So maybe the hooded man is a real person after
all.

00:22:10.779 --> 00:22:12.665
There’s no one answer to the mystery of
the Hooded Man.

00:22:12.665 --> 00:22:18.649
The man could be Harwin or Hal or maybe Robett
Glover, in a plot against the Boltons with

00:22:18.649 --> 00:22:20.370
Rowan and Crowfood and Stannis.

00:22:20.370 --> 00:22:25.940
But the murderers in Winterfell are probably
the wildlings and Big Walder, so it’s not

00:22:25.940 --> 00:22:28.600
clear what the hooded man does.

00:22:28.600 --> 00:22:34.390
The man might be a ghost or delusion, but
that theory has problems too.

00:22:34.390 --> 00:22:36.760
Maybe we’ll find out in the next book.

00:22:36.760 --> 00:22:38.980
Maybe we’ll never know the truth.

00:22:38.980 --> 00:22:41.830
But one thing is certain.

